Interface MetaDataContributer<T extends DataObject>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DataContributor<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CertificateComposite, MultiKeyComposite, OldSingleKeyComposite, PublicKeyComposite, SingleKeyComposite

    public interface MetaDataContributer<T extends DataObject>
extends DataContributor<T>
    Interface for providing machine readable MetaData This is usually implemented by a DataObjectFactory or Composite and is intended to build a Map of attributes that provide meta-data information about the target object. These will usually be added to a XML or JSON document describing the target The keys should be valid element/key names.
    See Also:
    SummaryContributer
